The paper discusses a social decision support system that aggregates the decisions of millions of individuals, which suggests a focus on social computing and artificial intelligence. The use of a multi-relational network ontology and grammar-based particle swarm algorithm also suggests a focus on data science and cybernetics. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SOC (Computational Social Science). Additionally, the use of algorithms and problem-solving techniques suggests a possible fit with cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
